# Tempo configuration — EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values.
# NEVER put real secrets in this file or commit a real `.env`. This is a PUBLIC
# repo. Settings are read by tempo/config.py via pydantic-settings; every key is
# prefixed with TEMPO_ and can also be set as an environment variable.

# ---- Runtime data location ----------------------------------------------------
# Root directory for secrets/state: the SQLite DB and OAuth tokens. Defaults to
# ~/.tempo/ — deliberately OUTSIDE the repo tree so an accidental `git add .` can
# never sweep up a secret or the database.
# Uncomment to override:
# TEMPO_DATA_DIR=~/.tempo

# ---- Content location (races, heat, reports) ---------------------------------
# The files you read/edit: races.md, heat.md, and generated reports/. Defaults to
# TEMPO_DATA_DIR. Point it at a GITIGNORED folder in the project (e.g. training/)
# to keep them handy alongside the code while the DB and tokens stay in DATA_DIR.
# This data is personal/health — the target MUST be gitignored (training/ is).
# TEMPO_CONTENT_DIR=~/Projects/tempo/training

# ---- Strava OAuth (Phase 2) ---------------------------------------------------
# Create an API application at https://www.strava.com/settings/api, then put the
# app's Client ID and Client Secret here. Run the one-time handshake with:
#   tempo strava auth            # prints the authorize URL
#   tempo strava auth --code XXX # completes it with the code from the redirect
# Tokens are then stored under TEMPO_DATA_DIR/tokens (mode 0600) and the rotating
# refresh token is persisted atomically, so you never re-auth.
TEMPO_STRAVA_CLIENT_ID=
TEMPO_STRAVA_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OAuth redirect URI. Only the host must match your Strava app's "Authorization
# Callback Domain"; localhost is fine for the manual copy-the-code flow.
# TEMPO_STRAVA_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost

# ---- Garmin Connect (Phase 6) -------------------------------------------------
# Your personal Garmin Connect login (sleep, HRV, resting HR, body battery,
# stress, steps), via the unofficial garminconnect library. Set these, then run
# the ONE-TIME interactive login:
#   tempo garmin login            # prompts for an MFA code if Garmin asks
# Session tokens are persisted under TEMPO_DATA_DIR/tokens/garmin (mode 0600) and
# REUSED on every later sync -- the scheduled job NEVER logs in again. This is
# deliberate: Garmin rate-limits logins per-account and repeated logins can lock
# you out for 48h+. If you ever see repeated 429s, STOP and wait hours -- do NOT
# retry (Tempo never retries a Garmin 429; it fails-logs-skips so Strava + analysis
# keep working).
TEMPO_GARMIN_EMAIL=
TEMPO_GARMIN_PASSWORD=

# ---- Telegram bot (v1.1 Phase 9) --------------------------------------------
# Owner-only Telegram bot that runs locally via long-polling (no webhook, no
# inbound ports). Phase 9 just wires the scaffold + /start; Phase 10 adds the
# voice-memo + agent loop. The bot will only ever reply to your own chat id --
# every other update is silently dropped at the filter level.
#
# The env-var names below are BARE (NOT prefixed with TEMPO_) so the standard
# Telegram convention is preserved.
#
# One-time setup:
#   1. In Telegram, search @BotFather -> /start -> /newbot. Pick a display name
#      and a username ending in `bot` (e.g. `tempo_<you>_bot`). BotFather replies
#      with an HTTP API token like `1234567890:AAH...` -- treat it as a password.
#   2. Find your own chat id: open a chat with your new bot, send any message
#      (e.g. `hi`), then in a browser visit
#          https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates
#      and read `result[0].message.chat.id` (a positive integer for a private
#      1-on-1 chat; if `result` is empty, send another message and refresh).
#   3. Fill in the two assignments below in your real `.env`, then run
#          chmod 600 .env
#      so other local users cannot read the token.
#   4. See docs/TELEGRAM_BOT.md (added in Phase 9 plan 09-02) for the long form,
#      the launchd autostart plist, and the operational runbook.
#
# If the token ever leaks: open @BotFather and /revoke to rotate it.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# TELEGRAM_OWNER_CHAT_ID=

# ---- Whisper transcription (v1.1 Phase 10) ------------------------------------
# faster-whisper runs LOCALLY on CPU (CTranslate2 has no Metal/MPS support on
# Mac). The defaults are tuned for an M-series laptop: small.en at int8 hits
# roughly 5-8x realtime, ~500 MB RAM, accurate enough for English voice memos.
# On Apple Silicon, `cpu` is the ONLY path that works -- `cuda` only on Linux+NVIDIA.
#
# Models you can swap to:
#   tiny.en          tiny    fast        less accurate
#   base.en          small   fast        ok
#   small.en         ~500MB  ~8-12s/60s  <-- DEFAULT, sweet spot
#   medium.en        ~1.5GB  ~20-30s/60s slow on CPU
#   large-v3-turbo   ~1.6GB  ~12-20s/60s slowest sane choice on CPU
#
# Env-var names are BARE (no TEMPO_ prefix), matching TELEGRAM_* above.
# WHISPER_MODEL_NAME=small.en
# WHISPER_COMPUTE_TYPE=int8
# WHISPER_DEVICE=cpu

# ---- Voice-file retention (v1.1 Phase 12) -------------------------------------
# How many days to keep cached voice memos in <content_dir>/voice/ after a
# successful transcription. Default 0 = delete immediately on success (the
# privacy-friendly choice). Set to a positive integer (e.g. 7) to keep voice
# files for N days so you can re-run transcription with a different model
# later. The bot sweeps stale files at startup. See docs/PRIVACY.md for the
# full contract; `tempo bot purge-voice` is the manual wipe hatch.
# VOICE_RETENTION_DAYS=0

# ---- Load & analysis settings (Phase 4) ---------------------------------------
# Per-activity training load is computed as rTSS (pace-based, primary) with an
# hrTSS fallback when pace/threshold is unavailable but HR is. If neither input
# is available a day is flagged "insufficient" rather than given an invented load.
#
# Threshold pace = the pace (seconds per km) you could hold all-out for ~1 hour.
# This is REQUIRED for rTSS. Example: 4:00/km = 240 ; 4:30/km = 270.
# TEMPO_THRESHOLD_PACE_S_PER_KM=240
#
# Heart-rate inputs power the hrTSS fallback (HR-reserve / Karvonen):
# TEMPO_MAX_HR=190
# TEMPO_RESTING_HR=50
# Lactate-threshold HR (the HR you could hold for ~1 hour). If unset it is
# estimated as ~0.92 * max_hr.
# TEMPO_THRESHOLD_HR=170
#
# Tracker files (read by analyses for context):
#   races.md  -- race-readiness context (PLAN-01)
#   heat.md   -- heat-adaptation sessions (recovery context)
# Tempo reads them from TEMPO_CONTENT_DIR (default ~/.tempo/). Copy the committed
# *.md.example templates there and edit them. These files are never committed.

# ---- Nutrition goal tracking (Phase 16) ---------------------------------------
# Optional daily kcal target. When set, the standalone `tempo analyze nutrition`
# report renders a `## Goal` section with the signed 7d delta, and the recovery
# report's `## Nutrition` section appends a target-vs-7d-average line. Silent
# (no warning, no error) when unset. See docs/NUTRITION.md.
# TEMPO_TARGET_KCAL=2200   # optional, enables goal tracking in nutrition + recovery reports
